Name:abs

Related:

Synopsis: &T <: num abs(&T <: num n)

Description: Absolute value of the number <tt>n</tt>. The result type is equal to the type of the argument <tt>n</tt>.

Examples:
<screen>
import Number;
abs(13)
abs(-13)
abs(3.14)
abs(-3.14)
</screen>

